<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7339> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7339" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "IIIIvir Monetalis. In MRR 2.440, and Index, 565, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.496, no. 485, 43 B.C. If the coins of Chilo could be dated earlier than 43 or 42 as in RE, it would be possible to identify him with the uncertain candidate Flaminius in 44 and the senator Cillo who perished in the proscriptions, but these identifications remain improbable. (RS, CP; TJC) See above, on *Cillo.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5980> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5980" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Perhaps the Flaminius whose candidacy for a vacancy in the college (caused by the death of Cinna?) was being supported by Octavian when Antony refused to allow the election to continue (App. BC 3.31; but note the senator Cillo who perished in the proscriptions, BC 4.27). According to Dio (45.6.3) and Plutarch (Ant. 16.2), Octavian was himself the candidate.]" .
